libmongo-client
------------------------------------------
This is an alternative C driver for MongoDB, with slightly different goals
than the official one:

libmongo-client is meant to be a stable (API, ABI and quality alike), clean,
well documented and well tested shared library, that strives to make the most
common use cases as convenient as possible.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.17-1
  gettext-0.18.1.1-2
  libgcc1-4.5.3-3
  libglib2.0-devel-2.32.4-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.32.4-1
  libiconv-1.14-2
  libpcre-devel-8.31-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-10-1
  automake-7-1
  binutils-2.22.51-2
  cygport-0.11.0-1
  gawk-4.0.1-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-3
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/algernon/libmongo-client

Canonical download:
  git://github.com/algernon/libmongo-client.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libmongo-client-0.1.6.1+git20121110-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libmongo-client-0.1.6.1+git20121110-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libmongo-client-0.1.6.1+git20121110-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libmongo-client-0.1.6.1+git20121110-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libmongo-client0-0.1.6.1+git20121110-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libmongo-client-devel-0.1.6.1+git20121110-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libmongo-client)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libmongo-client.README
